The paper discusses the combination of first-order logic and probability, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on Markov logic, which is a machine learning framework (cs.LG) that uses first-order logic as a template for features of Markov networks. The paper extends Markov logic to infinite domains, which involves concepts from probability theory (cs.IT) and statistical physics (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the structure of the set of consistent measures, which is related to the problem of satisfiability in first-order logic (cs.DS).
